### potential influence far beyond Russia and Ukraine

_ Joe Inwood _

_BBC reporter, once reported that Ukraine and African affairs_

Porigo may have retreated from the edge of the cliff, but the incident in the past 24 hours will fundamentally change his relationship with the President of Russia.

Pricigo has been known as the "Putin chef" for the catering industry. For many years, he and his Wagner's mercenaries have played a key role in Russia's foreign policy, although it is hidden.

In Putin's unable to publicize or unwilling to do publicly, Wagner was used to conduct military intervention.

For example, supporting Syrian President Bashar Assad and trying to interfere with the 2016 US elections on the Internet, Wagner has played an increasingly important role in some of the most chaotic places in the world.

But the place where the mercenary footprint is the most is Africa.

For example, in Mali, a coup in 2020 and 2021 witnessed the establishment of a military power, and Wagner participated in a large number of long -term Islamic rebellions. Although they thought they were there under the instructions of the Russian government, Wagner was really going to the local area.

In the Central and African Republic, it is said that they are helping the government, resisting the rebels, and defending the capital. Wagner is accused of having an invasion of human rights.

Given Vagna's may now seem to be excluded by the Kremlin, what will their soldiers in Africa and their government support?

In addition, Wagner also controls a large number of mineral resources, which is the source of most wealth of the organization.

Since Progojin has fallen out of favor, can he still maintain control of these resources?

