From 1993 to 2020, the United States' projects in Vietnam invested more than 166 million US dollars, focusing on the problems left over from the war, such as clearing landmines and unwnched bombs and providing explosive risk education.

During the formal visit to Vietnam in April, US Secretary of State Anthony Brinkeng said that Washington is committed to solving the problem of war.

