Like many countries in the region, Iraq's social contract is based on the recruitment of public sector. Citizens are expected to work in the public sector when graduating from college. Article 22 of the 2005 Constitution of Iraq stipulates the right to work. But people generally think this means government positions.

Since 2003, the public sector has increased four times, and current salary accounts for more than a quarter of the budget of 2023.

The way Iraqi Hussein formed after the steps of Sadam Hussein in 2003, as if the country can still afford this arrangement, and this is for political interests. In the Kurdish region of Iraq, we use the asylum network to establish contact and legitimacy with the people of the New Iraqi country.

